  "intent": "Step-by-step procedure for diagnosing why a Claude Code (or Codex / generic-provider) session has fewer rows in regin's session_spans table than the on-disk JSONL transcript implies, and for driving recovery. Triage starts in the hook activity log (feature=hooks) to confirm the turn_trace handler fired, then walks the ingest-errors log, the JSONL transcript, and the per-session seen-uuid cache. The recovery path is lib.trace.repair.repair_session_spans (also POST /api/sessions/<trace_id>/repair-spans), which trims the locked-out uuids, replays turn_trace's live emit pipeline, and materializes the healed projection. Verification reads back from session_spans and confirms the span_repair_completed activity-log row. Every step is shell + the regin venv.",
  "label": "Debug a missing trace span (hooks-log triage, ingest-errors, seen-uuid cache lockout, repair endpoint)",
